function maximumRemovals(s, p, removable) {
    let low = 0, high = removable.length;
    while (low < high) {
        let mid = Math.floor((low + high + 1) / 2);
        let temp_s = s.split('');
        for (let i = 0; i < mid; i++) {
            temp_s[removable[i]] = '-';
        }
        let i = 0, j = 0;
        while (i < temp_s.length && j < p.length) {
            if (temp_s[i] === p[j]) {
                j++;
            }
            i++;
        }
        if (j === p.length) {
            low = mid;
        } else {
            high = mid - 1;
        }
    }
    return low;
}
```


    We first initialize two variables low and high with values 0 and the length of the removable array.

We then enter a while loop. In that loop:
1. Calculate the mid using low and high.
2. Create a temporary string "temp_s" based on "s" for testing purposes.
3. Mark the character at the index in "temp_s" that's stored in the removable array for the first k indices.
4. Initialize two variables i and j with value 0.
5. Enter a while loop:
   a. Check if the character at index i in "temp_s" is equal to the character at index j in "p".
   b. If they are equal, increment the variable j.
   c. Increment the variable i.
6. Check if j is equal to the length of "p".
   a. If true, we set low = mid.
   b. If false, we set high = mid - 1.

After the loop, return the value of low which will be the maximum k such that p is still a subsequence of s after the removals.

